WEBVTT

00:00.117 --> 00:01.862
I really want
a tomorrow with you.

00:01.862 --> 00:03.454
Gary:
<i>When trust is broken...</i>

00:03.454 --> 00:05.996
Don't go. I need you
to help me get through this.

00:05.996 --> 00:07.372
<i>...it's hard to forgive...</i>

00:07.372 --> 00:08.634
What's going on?
Did he say?

00:08.634 --> 00:10.176
Gary: Elliot is not as open
with his family.

00:10.176 --> 00:11.261
You outed a 12‐year‐old.

00:11.261 --> 00:12.554
<i>...hard to rebuild...</i>

00:12.554 --> 00:14.681
Rome: But the money for
the restaurant came from Neil.

00:14.681 --> 00:15.932
Who's Neil?
Her uncle.

00:15.932 --> 00:17.100
<i>...hard to go on.</i>

00:17.100 --> 00:19.269
When I was younger,
I let him touch me.

00:19.269 --> 00:20.729
What he did
was sexual assault.

00:20.729 --> 00:23.106
<i>But somehow, we do.</i>

00:23.106 --> 00:24.649
I'm giving away the money
to a women's shelter.

00:24.649 --> 00:26.484
<i>We take a chance...</i>

00:26.484 --> 00:29.279
Your mom is sitting by herself
in a restaurant. Talk to her.

00:29.279 --> 00:30.280
Maggie.

00:30.280 --> 00:31.531
<i>...open our hearts...</i>

00:31.531 --> 00:33.116
Jon ‐‐ I just wish
I could talk to him.

00:33.116 --> 00:34.284
You have to
forgive yourself.

00:34.284 --> 00:36.703
<i>...and protect</i>
<i>what we have left.</i>

00:36.703 --> 00:37.537
Jon left you money.

00:37.537 --> 00:38.955
We don't want it.
Mitch.

00:38.955 --> 00:40.165
I don't want my son
finding out

00:40.165 --> 00:41.958
I've been lying to him
his whole life.

00:41.958 --> 00:43.335
I think
Jon might be my father.

00:45.628 --> 00:47.422
Rome: Hold on!
I shouldn't have said anything.
I got to go.

00:47.422 --> 00:49.049
[ Elevator bell dings ]
What the hell
are you talking about?

00:49.049 --> 00:50.675
You think that Jon
might be your father?

00:50.675 --> 00:52.135
Do not press that button.
[ Sighs ]

00:52.135 --> 00:54.721
PJ, talk to me.

00:54.721 --> 00:56.931
Tell me
what is going on.

00:56.931 --> 01:02.562
♪♪

01:02.562 --> 01:04.147
After...

01:04.147 --> 01:07.484
after Jon died...

01:07.484 --> 01:09.736
your friend Gary
came to our house.

01:09.736 --> 01:12.864
He was looking
for my mother.

01:12.864 --> 01:14.783
Your mom is
Barbara Morgan?

01:14.783 --> 01:15.992
It's Nelson now.

01:15.992 --> 01:17.327
And you're just
telling me that?

01:17.327 --> 01:19.204
I'm sorry.
It's just...

01:19.204 --> 01:21.790
[Sighs] it's been
a lot to handle.

01:21.790 --> 01:24.918
Look, when Gary came to
our house, looking for my mom,

01:24.918 --> 01:26.378
I‐I couldn't hear
what they were saying,

01:26.378 --> 01:29.047
but after he left,
my dad was pissed.

01:29.047 --> 01:30.256
Barbara: It's fine, Mitch.
He's gone.

01:30.256 --> 01:32.342
Mitch: What if Patrick
finds out? Huh?

01:32.342 --> 01:34.886
He can't know
we lied to him.

01:34.886 --> 01:37.972
Okay, s‐so maybe Mitch
isn't your biological father,

01:37.972 --> 01:39.557
but that guy Dave ‐‐

01:39.557 --> 01:40.850
he was your mother's boyfriend
back then.

01:40.850 --> 01:43.645
I‐I know,
but I found a video.

01:43.645 --> 01:46.314
I know about the video.
Dave was Jon's best friend.

01:46.314 --> 01:48.525
Have you seen it?

01:48.525 --> 01:50.777
<i>Barbara...</i>

01:50.777 --> 01:52.403
<i>as guilty as I felt</i>

01:52.403 --> 01:54.656
<i>for Dave getting on that plane</i>
<i>without me,</i>

01:54.656 --> 01:56.116
<i>I felt even worse</i>

01:56.116 --> 01:59.285
<i>for what happened after,</i>
<i>between us ‐‐</i>

01:59.285 --> 02:01.704
<i>not being there</i>
<i>for you and the baby.</i>

02:01.704 --> 02:04.207
<i>I left you.</i>

02:04.207 --> 02:06.668
<i>Just when you needed me most.</i>

02:06.668 --> 02:11.381
He kept apologizing,
like what he left her with...

02:11.381 --> 02:12.757
was me.

02:12.757 --> 02:15.176
I think something happened
between Jon and my mom

02:15.176 --> 02:16.803
after Dave died.

02:16.803 --> 02:18.805
That's why I was at
the hospital the day we met.

02:18.805 --> 02:22.142
I followed Gary there,
trying to find answers.

02:22.142 --> 02:24.185
But ‐‐ But instead,
I found your script.

02:26.146 --> 02:28.356
So, your whole act about being
depressed, that was just ‐‐

02:28.356 --> 02:30.108
No, no, no,
that was real.

02:30.108 --> 02:33.111
Your script ‐‐ so true to me,
a‐and it got me thinking.

02:33.111 --> 02:35.447
Jon obviously
suffered from depression,

02:35.447 --> 02:37.949
just like I do.

02:37.949 --> 02:40.452
M‐Maybe I got it
from him.

02:40.452 --> 02:43.121
It's just
another connection, right?

02:43.121 --> 02:46.458
I mean, why was leaving
a tape for my mom

02:46.458 --> 02:48.293
the last thing
that Jon did?

02:49.794 --> 02:51.963
That wasn't
the last thing Jon did.

02:53.381 --> 02:55.216
The last thing he did
was leave your mom

02:55.216 --> 02:56.801
a half a million dollars.

02:56.801 --> 02:58.803
♪♪

03:05.727 --> 03:08.730
[ Crickets chirping ]

03:15.778 --> 03:22.285
♪♪

03:22.285 --> 03:28.625
♪♪

03:28.625 --> 03:30.501
[ Children shouting playfully
in distance, dog barking ]

03:30.501 --> 03:33.796
Woman: Oh!
She's such a sweetie!

03:33.796 --> 03:35.340
Hi. [ Chuckles ]

03:35.340 --> 03:36.674
First time
at the park?

03:36.674 --> 03:39.260
Me? No, no.
[ Chuckles ]

03:39.260 --> 03:41.930
I used to come here a long time
ago with my other kids.

03:41.930 --> 03:43.681
Oh. Me too.

03:43.681 --> 03:45.183
So, not your first,
huh?

03:45.183 --> 03:46.017
No. [ Laughs ]

03:47.268 --> 03:48.728
How old's your baby?

03:48.728 --> 03:49.979
He's 9 months, but ‐‐
I can hold him
for a while, Mom.

03:49.979 --> 03:51.105
[ Chuckling ] Sure.

03:51.105 --> 03:52.857
[ Baby laughs ]

03:52.857 --> 03:57.320
♪♪

03:57.320 --> 03:58.446
<i>She's</i> my youngest.

03:59.656 --> 04:01.241
So, you're the grandma?

04:01.241 --> 04:04.118
Uh, I prefer "Lammy."

04:04.118 --> 04:05.411
[ Both chuckle ]

04:06.996 --> 04:08.248
Lammy.

04:08.248 --> 04:12.126
♪♪

04:12.126 --> 04:14.963
[ Birds chirping ]

04:19.259 --> 04:22.053
[ Metal clanking in distance ]

04:22.053 --> 04:23.846
Morning.

04:23.846 --> 04:25.682
Morning.

04:25.682 --> 04:26.891
[ Clanking continues ]

04:26.891 --> 04:28.643
Where's Theo?

04:28.643 --> 04:30.603
[ Groans ]

04:30.603 --> 04:32.772
[ Cereal pouring ]

04:35.108 --> 04:41.823
♪♪

04:41.823 --> 04:43.908
I was gonna make
banana pancakes,

04:43.908 --> 04:46.452
but then I realized
I'm only 9.

04:48.413 --> 04:50.498
There's always cereal.

04:50.498 --> 04:54.252
♪♪

04:54.252 --> 04:56.588
Delilah: <i>There is a mom here</i>
<i>whose dream is</i>

04:56.588 --> 04:59.340
to have three kids
before she's 30.

04:59.340 --> 05:01.384
Don't look directly
into their youthful glow.

05:01.384 --> 05:02.552
It'll blind you.

05:02.552 --> 05:03.553
[ Chuckles ]

05:03.553 --> 05:04.971
[ Call‐waiting beep ]

05:06.598 --> 05:09.058
Hey, Andrew's calling.
Should I take it?

05:09.058 --> 05:11.060
Yeah. It's all good.

05:11.060 --> 05:12.854
I'm actually meeting
with him later.

05:12.854 --> 05:13.980
<i>Tell him I'm on my way.</i>

05:13.980 --> 05:15.732
Okay. Bye.

05:16.941 --> 05:18.234
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:18.234 --> 05:19.485
Hi.

05:19.485 --> 05:20.737
How's Charlie?

05:20.737 --> 05:22.697
Well, uh,
don't want to jinx it.

05:22.697 --> 05:24.240
[ Laughs ]
<i>[ Laughs ] Good.</i>

05:24.240 --> 05:25.867
<i>So, um, I have</i>
<i>this meeting with Regina.</i>

05:25.867 --> 05:28.494
I realized that you haven't
been down here in a while.

05:28.494 --> 05:29.704
Do you want
to maybe catch up?

05:29.704 --> 05:31.247
<i>Like, say, tonight?</i>

05:32.498 --> 05:33.708
Tonight?
<i>Yeah.</i>

05:33.708 --> 05:36.669
I mean...yeah,
I happen to be free, and...

05:36.669 --> 05:39.380
<i>um...I know that you've been</i>
<i>up to your neck in diapers,</i>

05:39.380 --> 05:41.382
so I‐I thought you might enjoy
some grown‐up time.

05:41.382 --> 05:44.260
I mean, n‐not "grown‐up time,"
but, you know...

05:44.260 --> 05:45.928
<i>You know, "time away</i>
<i>from the baby" time.</i>

05:45.928 --> 05:47.263
I mean, not ‐‐ not that
you don't love your baby.

05:47.263 --> 05:49.015
I'd love to.

05:49.015 --> 05:51.142
Dinner sounds nice.
[ Chuckles ]

05:51.142 --> 05:53.102
Wait, Sophie's
camping this weekend,

05:53.102 --> 05:55.229
so just let me see
if I can find a sitter.

05:55.229 --> 05:56.856
<i>Okay. Bye.</i>
Yeah.

05:56.856 --> 05:58.316
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:58.316 --> 05:59.359
[ Laughs ]

05:59.359 --> 06:00.276
[ Chuckles ]

06:03.696 --> 06:06.616
♪♪

06:06.616 --> 06:08.493
[ Keyboard clicks ]

06:08.493 --> 06:14.916
♪♪

06:14.916 --> 06:17.377
Gina, have you seen
my script?

06:17.377 --> 06:18.670
I looked everywhere.
I‐I thought ‐‐

06:18.670 --> 06:19.504
Um...

06:19.504 --> 06:21.214
Oh. Thanks.

06:21.214 --> 06:23.466
Why are you nervous?
You've known Todd for years.

06:23.466 --> 06:25.551
Yeah, and I'm pretty sure
he hasn't even read it.

06:25.551 --> 06:28.554
Big‐time Hollywood producer ‐‐
why would he actually read it?

06:28.554 --> 06:30.306
He's only in town
because the Lakers are
playing the Celtics.

06:30.306 --> 06:32.141
Babe.

06:32.141 --> 06:34.268
Oh, the shelter's
having a benefit.

06:34.268 --> 06:35.395
I'm proud of you, babe.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.230
Thanks.

06:37.230 --> 06:38.606
I probably won't have
time to go, though.

06:38.606 --> 06:39.607
Why not?

06:39.607 --> 06:41.150
Oh. I'm late.

06:41.150 --> 06:42.276
Got to meet Andrew.

06:42.276 --> 06:43.653
Might want to put
your mouthguard in.

06:44.862 --> 06:45.822
You're grinding
your teeth.

06:45.822 --> 06:48.157
[ Chuckles ]
Look, I made a deal.

06:48.157 --> 06:50.076
I gave all that money
to the Women's Shelter,

06:50.076 --> 06:52.495
and if, you know,
that means if I have to

06:52.495 --> 06:54.747
be in business with Andrew,
so be it.

06:54.747 --> 06:56.833
I almost wish your un‐‐

06:56.833 --> 06:58.042
Neil...

06:58.042 --> 06:59.419
had lived long enough
to see

06:59.419 --> 07:01.462
what you actually did
with his money.

07:01.462 --> 07:03.464
Poetic justice ‐‐
know what I'm saying?

07:05.383 --> 07:07.135
I'm sorry.

07:07.135 --> 07:08.553
I should‐‐ I shouldn't
have said that.

07:08.553 --> 07:10.304
What? The truth?

07:11.639 --> 07:12.640
Love you.

07:12.640 --> 07:13.850
Love you, too.

07:15.643 --> 07:17.145
[ Door closes ]

07:17.145 --> 07:19.147
[ Footsteps approach,
door closes ]

07:24.861 --> 07:25.987
May I ask a question?

07:25.987 --> 07:27.488
[ Refrigerator door slams ]

07:27.488 --> 07:28.656
[ Bottle thuds ]

07:29.949 --> 07:31.534
May I make an observation?

07:31.534 --> 07:32.535
[ Cabinet door slams ]

07:34.120 --> 07:36.372
[ Bowl thuds ]
You know, your mom left
at 5:30 this morning.

07:36.372 --> 07:37.957
[ Silverware clatters ]
The reason I know that

07:37.957 --> 07:39.917
[ Drawer closes ]
is because
my dear friend Colin...

07:39.917 --> 07:42.253
[ Whimpers ]
...wanted to be walked
at 5:31.

07:42.253 --> 07:44.630
And what time does
your detective agency open?
[ Bottle thuds ]

07:44.630 --> 07:47.175
Well, according to
this note, she's at your
old apartment, right?

07:47.175 --> 07:48.801
So that could mean
one of two things.

07:48.801 --> 07:50.678
Either last night
brought you two together

07:50.678 --> 07:52.013
and she's staying in town

07:52.013 --> 07:53.181
to build on
that incredible foundation

07:53.181 --> 07:54.182
or ‐‐

07:54.182 --> 07:56.017
[ Cabinet door slams ]

07:56.017 --> 07:57.226
...that.

07:57.226 --> 07:58.269
Are you mad at me?

07:58.269 --> 07:59.312
I'm trying to figure out

07:59.312 --> 08:01.147
how I could have
possibly screwed up.

08:01.147 --> 08:03.191
Not everything's
about you, Gary.

08:03.191 --> 08:04.567
[ Container thuds ]

08:04.567 --> 08:05.568
Maybe...
[ Lid thuds ]

08:05.568 --> 08:07.236
...you're a <i>little</i> mad
at me?

08:07.236 --> 08:09.530
I took your advice,
and I went to go meet with her.

08:09.530 --> 08:11.115
She was not there alone.

08:11.115 --> 08:13.034
She was with a man.

08:13.034 --> 08:14.994
Okay.

08:14.994 --> 08:16.120
Uh, what ‐‐
what kind of man?

08:16.120 --> 08:17.246
The kind you hug,

08:17.246 --> 08:19.290
the kind you seem
incredibly happy to see.

08:19.290 --> 08:21.125
Was it
her real estate agent?

08:21.125 --> 08:22.668
Do you brush the hair

08:22.668 --> 08:25.630
off of your
real estate agent's forehead?

08:25.630 --> 08:27.173
[ Spoon thuds ]

08:27.173 --> 08:28.382
You think it was a date?

08:29.716 --> 08:31.051
<i>You</i> said it.
I didn't.

08:31.051 --> 08:32.386
Well, how did she
introduce him?

08:32.386 --> 08:34.805
I don't ‐‐ I didn't stay.
I left.

08:34.805 --> 08:36.306
[ Refrigerator door closes ]

08:36.306 --> 08:38.809
Well, whatever it was,
she and your dad are
separated, right?

08:38.809 --> 08:41.061
So maybe she's just
testing out her market value.

08:41.061 --> 08:42.604
He was like 35.

08:42.604 --> 08:44.481
That's pretty good
market value.

08:44.481 --> 08:45.524
That's not funny!

08:45.524 --> 08:47.359
Now I <i>am</i> mad at you.

08:47.359 --> 08:49.153
God, I am such an idiot!

08:49.153 --> 08:50.154
Why?

08:50.154 --> 08:51.905
Because you actually
had me believing

08:51.905 --> 08:54.158
that she was here
to see <i>me.</i>

08:54.158 --> 08:56.201
♪♪

08:56.201 --> 08:57.244
[ Sighs ]

08:59.368 --> 09:00.669
[ Door closes ]

09:03.288 --> 09:05.915
So, these are all just ideas,
so you can always say no.

09:05.915 --> 09:08.463
These are the produce suppliers
I'd like you to talk to.

09:08.463 --> 09:09.716
No.

09:10.465 --> 09:11.966
I mean, maybe.

09:11.966 --> 09:14.469
I've...been working with
the same organic farm

09:14.469 --> 09:16.221
since my first restaurant.

09:16.221 --> 09:17.430
We're friends.

09:17.430 --> 09:18.765
I understand,
and this is not an edict,

09:18.765 --> 09:21.101
but, um, my guys
are organic, too.

09:21.101 --> 09:23.770
They're just a bigger operation,
so they're cheaper.

09:25.105 --> 09:27.357
Okay. Makes sense.
[ Chuckles ]

09:27.357 --> 09:28.900
Okay, yes,
I will call them.

09:28.900 --> 09:29.901
What else?

09:29.901 --> 09:31.361
I'd like to set up
a meeting

09:31.361 --> 09:33.488
between you and a social media
consultant ‐‐ Ken.

09:33.488 --> 09:35.907
Uh, this is his website.

09:35.907 --> 09:36.950
I already spoke to him
about you.

09:38.576 --> 09:39.786
Nothing but raves.

09:40.995 --> 09:42.539
Um, so...

09:42.539 --> 09:43.832
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:43.832 --> 09:45.417
...can we talk
about the menu?

09:47.252 --> 09:49.337
Mm‐hmm.
[ Clears throat ]

09:49.337 --> 09:51.506
One thing that everyone loves
is burgers and fries.

09:51.506 --> 09:54.926
Don't get me wrong ‐‐
I love a good burger.

09:54.926 --> 09:57.137
But it's not this restaurant,
so...no.

09:57.137 --> 09:58.805
Yes.

09:58.805 --> 10:01.141
But, you know,
you do lasagna,

10:01.141 --> 10:02.851
and you're not
an Italian restaurant.

10:02.851 --> 10:04.102
Lasagna was
Jon's favorite.

10:04.102 --> 10:04.894
Jon?

10:04.894 --> 10:06.020
Oh, you mean Delilah's ‐‐

10:07.355 --> 10:08.857
Yeah, okay, we can
forget about burgers.

10:08.857 --> 10:09.983
[ Sighs ]

10:09.983 --> 10:11.401
These are just ideas.

10:11.401 --> 10:14.070
Okay. Well, we should probably
run this by Delilah, so...

10:14.070 --> 10:14.988
Yeah, I'll tell her later,
when I see her.

10:16.531 --> 10:18.032
When are you seeing her?

10:18.032 --> 10:19.617
Uh, well, uh...

10:19.617 --> 10:21.035
[ Chuckles ]

10:21.035 --> 10:22.245
Regina: <i>I was there,</i>
<i>and I saw his face,</i>

10:22.245 --> 10:23.705
[ Door opens ]
<i>and it sounded like</i>
<i>a date.</i>

10:23.705 --> 10:26.166
What?! No!
It's not a date!

10:26.166 --> 10:28.460
<i>Look, D, if you and Andrew</i>
<i>want to go on a date,</i>

10:28.460 --> 10:29.794
<i>God bless.</i>
Aww.

10:29.794 --> 10:32.130
[ Sighing ] Oh, Gary's here.
I gotta go.

10:32.130 --> 10:33.715
<i>Oh.</i>
<i>Have fun with Andrew.</i>

10:33.715 --> 10:35.425
Hello.

10:35.425 --> 10:38.178
I don't know what you think
is going on, but it's not.

10:38.178 --> 10:39.596
But I think you <i>do</i> know
what I think is going on,

10:39.596 --> 10:40.597
and it <i>is.</i>

10:40.597 --> 10:41.598
Drop it.

10:41.598 --> 10:43.057
Consider it dropped.

10:43.057 --> 10:44.559
Where's he taking you?

10:44.559 --> 10:46.811
Huh.
I didn't drop it.

10:46.811 --> 10:48.563
I got these here diapers.

10:48.563 --> 10:50.148
I'll deliver 'em,
but I will not change them.

10:50.148 --> 10:51.316
Thank you.

10:51.316 --> 10:53.777
Actually,
<i>could</i> you change them?

10:53.777 --> 10:55.945
Because I need a sitter
for tonight.

10:55.945 --> 10:56.946
For your date?

10:56.946 --> 10:57.989
We're just going to dinner

10:57.989 --> 10:59.866
so he can fill me in
on the restaurant.

10:59.866 --> 11:01.576
Say it's a date,
and I'll babysit.

11:01.576 --> 11:02.827
[ Charlie cooing ]

11:02.827 --> 11:04.788
I don't know what it is.

11:04.788 --> 11:07.582
♪♪

11:07.582 --> 11:08.625
Well, <i>I</i> do.

11:11.294 --> 11:12.712
It's a date.

11:14.631 --> 11:16.216
[ Chuckles ]
Where's Danny?

11:16.216 --> 11:18.676
While I'm here, I want to say hi
to my 12‐year‐old friend.

11:21.262 --> 11:23.723
[ <i>"Greased Lightnin'" plays</i> ]

11:26.434 --> 11:28.019
Danny: ♪ With a four‐speed
on the floor ♪

11:28.019 --> 11:29.479
♪ They'll be waitin'
at the door ♪

11:29.479 --> 11:31.022
♪ You know without a doubt ♪

11:31.022 --> 11:33.358
♪ We'll be really makin' out
in Greased Lightnin' ♪

11:33.358 --> 11:35.401
What...are you doing?

11:35.401 --> 11:36.694
[ Music stops ]

11:36.694 --> 11:38.238
I like it,
but what are you doing?

11:38.238 --> 11:39.364
Nothing.

11:39.364 --> 11:41.324
Spill it. Pronto.

11:41.324 --> 11:43.868
I was just practicing...

11:43.868 --> 11:45.495
a song.

11:45.495 --> 11:46.788
"Greased Lightnin'."

11:48.122 --> 11:49.499
I might have been...

11:49.499 --> 11:51.543
called back.

11:51.543 --> 11:53.294
For what?

11:53.294 --> 11:55.380
School musical?

11:55.380 --> 11:57.006
You guys are doing
"Grease," huh?

11:57.006 --> 11:58.716
Quiet!

11:58.716 --> 12:00.593
I don't want Mom
to know.

12:00.593 --> 12:02.262
Why?

12:02.262 --> 12:06.224
Because if I do a musical,
kids might think I'm gay.

12:06.224 --> 12:07.600
You <i>are</i> gay.

12:07.600 --> 12:09.352
You know that,
and my family knows that,

12:09.352 --> 12:12.772
but the kids at school
don't.

12:12.772 --> 12:14.774
I don't want to be
the first one to come out.

12:17.652 --> 12:21.114
I'll be "the gay kid"
for the rest of my school life.

12:21.114 --> 12:23.157
[ Sighs ]

12:23.157 --> 12:25.285
This is why high school
musicals aren't as good
as they could be.

12:27.412 --> 12:29.706
Straight dudes
do musicals, too.

12:29.706 --> 12:32.250
Nobody can put you in a box
but <i>you,</i> Danny.

12:32.250 --> 12:33.543
<i>I</i> did "Grease."

12:33.543 --> 12:35.670
Everybody in high school
does "Grease."

12:35.670 --> 12:38.339
I was in the chorus,
but I still know all the moves.

12:38.339 --> 12:40.049
Don't tell Rome.
He thinks he's a dancer.

12:40.049 --> 12:41.718
But this...

12:41.718 --> 12:42.677
this is Broadway.

12:44.053 --> 12:46.681
Now, I'm babysitting
tonight,

12:46.681 --> 12:49.100
but after
Charlie goes down...

12:49.100 --> 12:50.560
I'm all yours.

12:50.560 --> 12:53.021
But, Gary, the callbacks
are <i>tonight.</i>

12:53.021 --> 12:55.064
Well, then, we better
get started soon.

12:55.064 --> 12:56.858
Hey, I'll be back later.

12:56.858 --> 12:58.067
We got this.

12:58.067 --> 12:59.861
E‐Em, actually,
I don't know if I want to ‐‐

12:59.861 --> 13:01.946
Later.
Okay.

13:01.946 --> 13:03.907
Rome: Thanks for lunch, man.
It was really great.

13:03.907 --> 13:05.491
Todd: I already told you
what's great ‐‐

13:05.491 --> 13:07.285
that script of yours.

13:07.285 --> 13:08.536
Appreciate it, man.

13:08.536 --> 13:10.330
The characters are real,
you know?

13:10.330 --> 13:12.957
A‐And seeing guys
talking openly.

13:12.957 --> 13:14.500
Thank you.
And it was funny.

13:14.500 --> 13:16.836
Honestly, I almost cried
at one point.

13:16.836 --> 13:18.546
Really?
[ Sighs ]

13:18.546 --> 13:19.797
Look, I don't want
to be that guy.

13:19.797 --> 13:20.965
It's just...

13:20.965 --> 13:22.926
the suicide thing.

13:22.926 --> 13:24.135
That's a tough sell.

13:24.135 --> 13:25.720
Why suicide?

13:27.347 --> 13:29.891
I d‐‐ I just ‐‐
I just thought it was timely.

13:29.891 --> 13:31.601
Maybe, uh, I don't know,
you could ‐‐

13:31.601 --> 13:33.770
You could give the guy
some kind of athletic injury

13:33.770 --> 13:35.647
to overcome
or something like that.

13:35.647 --> 13:37.523
People love an underdog,
you know?

13:37.523 --> 13:38.608
No, no, I can ‐‐

13:38.608 --> 13:40.151
Rome?
Yo?

13:40.151 --> 13:42.111
Damn,
this is so kismet.

13:42.111 --> 13:44.030
Hey, look, I literally
just lost a director

13:44.030 --> 13:45.156
for this commercial ‐‐

13:45.156 --> 13:47.241
this Lexus commercial
that starts ‐‐

13:47.241 --> 13:49.160
I'm sorry.
Excuse me, man.
No, no, it's all good.
It's all good.

13:49.160 --> 13:50.662
Hey, hey, hey. Don,
this is my boy Todd Pilzner.

13:50.662 --> 13:51.996
It's a pleasure.
[ Horn honks ]

13:51.996 --> 13:53.247
Uh...listen,

13:53.247 --> 13:55.792
I'm telling you,
make those changes, okay?

13:55.792 --> 13:56.918
I'll think about it.
I will.

13:56.918 --> 13:58.753
No, no, don't think ‐‐
do.

13:58.753 --> 14:00.088
'Cause I don't really like
many scripts,

14:00.088 --> 14:02.131
and I never
almost cry, so...

14:02.131 --> 14:03.341
[ Laughs ]

14:03.341 --> 14:04.592
He's, uh,
he's a producer?

14:04.592 --> 14:06.010
Big‐time.

14:06.010 --> 14:08.304
Dude, I wish
I could help you out,

14:08.304 --> 14:10.765
but I am very close to getting
what I've always wanted.

14:10.765 --> 14:12.892
Rome, look ‐‐
No, no, dude, seriously,

14:12.892 --> 14:14.811
good luck on
your commercial, man.

14:14.811 --> 14:16.270
Alright? Really.

14:20.775 --> 14:21.984
Hey.

14:21.984 --> 14:23.820
Auggie's mom
just texted me.

14:23.820 --> 14:26.698
He wants Theo to come over
for a sleepover tonight.

14:26.698 --> 14:28.825
But he's never
done one before.

14:28.825 --> 14:30.827
He still sleeps
with a flashlight.

14:30.827 --> 14:32.829
I know.
He's never gonna go.

14:35.415 --> 14:36.624
[ Knock on door ]

14:38.918 --> 14:40.169
I have brought you
a peace offering.

14:40.169 --> 14:41.754
[ Sighs ]
[ Door closes ]

14:41.754 --> 14:44.966
This is a $12 soy latte.

14:44.966 --> 14:46.426
You should have seen
the little heart

14:46.426 --> 14:47.844
on the top of that thing.

14:47.844 --> 14:50.638
Okay, I'm sure it was beautiful,
but I have a patient coming.

14:50.638 --> 14:51.639
You have to go.

14:51.639 --> 14:53.182
Don't worry.

14:53.182 --> 14:54.976
As soon as that green light
goes on, I'm out of here.

14:54.976 --> 14:56.686
So, how does this work,
exactly?

14:56.686 --> 14:58.104
People just open up to you

14:58.104 --> 14:59.897
the second
their asses hit the couch?

15:01.190 --> 15:03.484
Okay,
here's the deal, Doc.

15:03.484 --> 15:04.861
I messed up with my girl.

15:04.861 --> 15:06.237
Gary ‐‐
Nope.

15:06.237 --> 15:07.572
You're gonna want
to write some of this down.

15:07.572 --> 15:08.823
[ Sighs ]

15:10.658 --> 15:11.743
[ Groans ]

15:13.286 --> 15:14.495
What are you doing?

15:14.495 --> 15:15.830
I'm going
to a sleepover.

15:15.830 --> 15:17.707
Auggie asked me
yesterday at school.

15:17.707 --> 15:19.167
His mom was
supposed to text you.

15:20.793 --> 15:21.711
Yeah, she did.

15:23.087 --> 15:25.173
Um...

15:25.173 --> 15:27.008
Hey, bud...

15:27.008 --> 15:28.676
are you sure
you want to do this?

15:28.676 --> 15:31.804
Yeah.
I can't wait.

15:31.804 --> 15:33.681
What are you guys gonna do
while I'm gone?

15:33.681 --> 15:36.559
You should maybe go to a movie.
That would be fun, right?

15:36.559 --> 15:42.231
♪♪

15:42.231 --> 15:44.776
So...[ Sighs ]

15:44.776 --> 15:46.694
I got my girlfriend
into this thing,

15:46.694 --> 15:48.780
this terrible thing
with her mother.

15:48.780 --> 15:52.241
I was only trying to help,
but, truth be told,

15:52.241 --> 15:55.286
this is the first time
I've ever lived with a woman.

15:55.286 --> 15:56.746
We're having
some growing pains.

16:00.750 --> 16:03.169
And why do you think
that is?

16:03.169 --> 16:05.087
I don't know.

16:05.087 --> 16:07.423
She moved into my place
instead of the other way around.

16:07.423 --> 16:08.800
That's a thing.

16:08.800 --> 16:10.593
No, I mean,
why is it your first time

16:10.593 --> 16:12.762
ever living with a woman?

16:15.056 --> 16:16.349
Fair question.

16:16.349 --> 16:17.892
I don't know.

16:17.892 --> 16:20.186
I'm a great guy,
very loveable,

16:20.186 --> 16:21.646
killer beard.

16:21.646 --> 16:24.607
I mean, you just met me,
but...you get it.

16:24.607 --> 16:27.235
Unfortunately for you,
I'm not currently available.

16:27.235 --> 16:29.111
May I offer
a professional opinion?

16:29.111 --> 16:31.864
Yes. That's why I pay you
in $12 lattes.

16:31.864 --> 16:33.908
What I am seeing
is someone who is trying

16:33.908 --> 16:37.119
to fix something
that is not his to fix.

16:37.119 --> 16:38.621
Yes, maybe.

16:38.621 --> 16:41.457
But there's real stuff going on
with her and her mom.

16:41.457 --> 16:43.835
She needs to address it.
I want to bring it up.

16:43.835 --> 16:45.127
I don't want to touch
the third rail.

16:45.127 --> 16:46.462
Interesting.

16:46.462 --> 16:48.631
And while we're <i>not</i> touching
the third rail,

16:48.631 --> 16:49.966
have you ever thought

16:49.966 --> 16:52.343
that your problems
living with women

16:52.343 --> 16:54.136
might be
about <i>your</i> mother?

16:56.055 --> 16:57.390
My mother?

16:57.390 --> 17:00.142
Gary, she left right after
your 9th birthday party.

17:00.142 --> 17:02.687
And I still don't like her.
Or magicians.

17:02.687 --> 17:04.939
But we're here
to talk about <i>your</i> mom.

17:04.939 --> 17:07.942
But as your doctor, I would
rather talk about <i>yours.</i>

17:07.942 --> 17:09.777
Ennnnnh!
Not interested.

17:11.279 --> 17:13.865
That is because
there is stuff going on

17:13.865 --> 17:17.451
with <i>your</i> mom
that <i>you</i> haven't addressed.

17:17.451 --> 17:18.744
Okay, game over.

17:19.787 --> 17:20.788
[ Sighs ]

17:20.788 --> 17:21.831
Unh! Unh!

17:21.831 --> 17:23.875
Would you look at that.

17:23.875 --> 17:25.293
My cue
to get the hell out of here.

17:25.293 --> 17:26.210
[ Sighs ]

17:26.210 --> 17:27.587
Good session.

17:27.587 --> 17:28.963
I'm glad we all agree
I'm perfect,

17:28.963 --> 17:30.506
but you need
to call your mother.

17:30.506 --> 17:31.674
Goodbye.
[ Door closes ]

17:35.132 --> 17:37.009
Alright,
please take the line.

17:37.009 --> 17:40.429
[ Indistinct talking ]

17:40.429 --> 17:43.305
Hi. Wendy Cruz
from the Women's Shelter.

17:43.305 --> 17:44.422
Yes. Of course. Hi.

17:44.422 --> 17:45.839
I'm sorry to bother you.

17:45.839 --> 17:49.338
Um, I just wanted to personally
thank you for all the ‐‐

17:49.338 --> 17:52.592
No. Thank <i>you</i>
for all your incredible work.

17:52.592 --> 17:55.011
We were sad to hear that you
weren't coming to the benefit.

17:55.011 --> 17:56.804
Me too.

17:56.804 --> 17:59.515
You know, restaurants,
they're a lot, and I...

17:59.515 --> 18:00.683
Of course.

18:00.683 --> 18:03.603
Uh, this...

18:03.603 --> 18:05.855
is for you.

18:05.855 --> 18:08.858
We thought it'd be nice for you
to see how much you're helping.

18:08.858 --> 18:11.861
♪♪

18:11.861 --> 18:13.285
I know you want
to be anonymous,

18:13.285 --> 18:16.229
but we're about to go to print
with our programs,

18:16.229 --> 18:17.545
and I thought...

18:17.545 --> 18:21.192
you might want
to be included.

18:22.175 --> 18:25.659
I just don't think
it should be about <i>me.</i>

18:25.659 --> 18:27.336
That's all.

18:27.336 --> 18:28.980
Thank you.

18:36.028 --> 18:38.392
So quiet in here.

18:38.392 --> 18:39.184
Yeah.

18:43.355 --> 18:44.898
♪♪

18:44.898 --> 18:46.400
Katherine:
Look what we did!

18:46.400 --> 18:47.443
[ Chuckles ]

18:47.443 --> 18:49.194
Must have been
from my button.

18:49.194 --> 18:50.320
I love it.

18:52.364 --> 18:55.325
Every time we look at it,
we're gonna remember tonight.

18:55.325 --> 18:57.619
♪ Yeah, you'll be kicked around,
but get up ♪

19:00.622 --> 19:02.207
[ Inhales deeply ]

19:02.207 --> 19:03.500
Wanna go out to eat?

19:03.500 --> 19:04.334
I'll get my coat.

19:10.090 --> 19:12.176
I got you
a little something.

19:12.176 --> 19:15.137
I shouldn't try
to fix everything. I know.

19:15.137 --> 19:17.347
Don't audition
if you don't want to.

19:17.347 --> 19:19.433
That's the new rule.

19:19.433 --> 19:20.559
It's up to you.

19:22.144 --> 19:23.729
This jacket's
actually really cool.

19:23.729 --> 19:25.689
Yeah, don't put it
anywhere near an open flame.

19:26.899 --> 19:28.650
The thing is...

19:28.650 --> 19:32.529
part of me really <i>does</i> want
to get this part.

19:32.529 --> 19:34.698
It's just...

19:34.698 --> 19:37.534
Elliot got called back
for Kenickie, too.

19:37.534 --> 19:40.037
Your ex Elliot?

19:40.037 --> 19:42.289
We weren't
exactly a couple.

19:42.289 --> 19:45.000
Because he was too afraid
to be a couple.

19:45.000 --> 19:48.253
♪♪

19:48.253 --> 19:51.256
Well, it's between him and me
for this part now.

19:51.256 --> 19:53.467
Okay.

19:53.467 --> 19:55.969
Historically, I admit,
I'm not great at relationships,

19:55.969 --> 19:58.138
but I <i>really</i> hit my stride
when they're over.

19:58.138 --> 19:59.223
[ Chuckles ]

19:59.223 --> 20:00.599
Here's the secret ‐‐

20:00.599 --> 20:04.019
<i>never</i> let them think
they're doing better than you.

20:04.019 --> 20:06.772
So, why don't you put on
that dope jacket,

20:06.772 --> 20:09.024
and let's show 'em all
how great you are.

20:09.024 --> 20:16.073
♪♪

20:19.368 --> 20:20.536
Hey, Mom,
can I talk to you?

20:20.536 --> 20:21.578
Of course, honey.

20:21.578 --> 20:22.955
I‐I applied to RISD.

20:22.955 --> 20:25.165
[ Gasps ]
You did, sweetie?

20:25.165 --> 20:26.542
I didn't know that.

20:26.542 --> 20:28.252
Yeah, I‐I didn't ‐‐
didn't tell you guys

20:28.252 --> 20:29.795
'cause I‐I know how Dad feels
about art school.

20:31.129 --> 20:32.923
Well, what about <i>me?</i>

20:32.923 --> 20:34.007
Hmm?

20:35.759 --> 20:38.428
Look, your dad is just worried
about you making a living.

20:38.428 --> 20:40.013
That's all.

20:40.013 --> 20:42.558
But you are a great artist ‐‐
better than me.

20:42.558 --> 20:45.102
So if you get in...

20:45.102 --> 20:46.353
I think you should go.

20:46.353 --> 20:49.106
♪♪

20:49.106 --> 20:50.941
Yeah,
t‐t‐that's the thing.

20:50.941 --> 20:52.568
I‐I applied
for some scholarships,

20:52.568 --> 20:55.487
but they're
really competitive.

20:55.487 --> 20:57.322
Is there any way that you guys
could help me out?

20:57.322 --> 21:00.200
♪♪

21:00.200 --> 21:02.494
Or I‐I mean, is there anything
you guys, like, put aside

21:02.494 --> 21:04.496
or...I don't know...

21:04.496 --> 21:06.957
any extra savings?

21:06.957 --> 21:08.584
And what would we
tell Patrick

21:08.584 --> 21:10.419
about how we suddenly
came into that kind of cash?

21:10.419 --> 21:12.838
[ Sighs ]

21:12.838 --> 21:14.756
No, honey.

21:14.756 --> 21:17.009
You know we don't have
that kind of money.

21:17.009 --> 21:19.720
Yeah, I know.
I just thought I'd ask.

21:19.720 --> 21:24.349
♪♪

21:24.349 --> 21:27.144
[ Sighs ]

21:27.144 --> 21:29.521
♪ ...four‐speed on the floor,
they'll be waiting at the door ♪

21:29.521 --> 21:31.815
♪ You know without a doubt,
we'll be really makin' out ♪

21:31.815 --> 21:32.774
♪ In Greased Lightnin' ♪

21:32.774 --> 21:33.859
Step, touch,
step, touch.

21:33.859 --> 21:35.569
Drive the car, and...

21:35.569 --> 21:36.945
♪ Go, Greased Lightnin' ♪

21:36.945 --> 21:37.946
Stop, stop.
[ Music stops ]

21:37.946 --> 21:39.197
You're phoning it in,
Danny.

21:39.197 --> 21:40.991
What's with the jelly arm?
What is that, huh?

21:41.950 --> 21:43.702
You got to commit,
Kenickie.

21:43.702 --> 21:45.662
You're holding back, man!

21:45.662 --> 21:47.998
Don't be scared
of being yourself, okay?

21:47.998 --> 21:52.044
I'm <i>terrified</i>
of being myself.

21:52.044 --> 21:59.468
♪♪

21:59.468 --> 22:01.011
[ Sighs ]

22:01.011 --> 22:02.804
[ Tapping ]

22:02.804 --> 22:06.558
[ Patricia crying,
sighs ]

22:06.558 --> 22:08.226
[ Door closes ]

22:08.226 --> 22:10.145
Mom?

22:10.145 --> 22:11.355
I'm sorry.

22:13.607 --> 22:16.068
I'm ‐‐ I just...

22:16.068 --> 22:20.030
wish everybody knew
just how sorry I am.

22:20.030 --> 22:23.700
I‐I don't regret
knowing you...

22:23.700 --> 22:26.161
Eric...

22:26.161 --> 22:28.413
or...what we have.

22:28.413 --> 22:30.666
What I regret is...

22:30.666 --> 22:31.541
hurting people.

22:31.541 --> 22:32.668
Unbelievable.

22:32.668 --> 22:33.585
[ Gasps ]

22:34.711 --> 22:37.005
I‐I‐I ‐‐ I have to go.

22:38.298 --> 22:40.217
What the hell
is going on?

22:40.217 --> 22:41.510
Mom, who is Eric?

22:41.510 --> 22:43.303
He's, um...

22:44.513 --> 22:45.514
He's a friend.

22:45.514 --> 22:46.807
A friend?

22:46.807 --> 22:49.518
Yeah, we met...
about a month ago.

22:49.518 --> 22:51.144
A‐Are you seeing
this guy?

22:51.144 --> 22:52.979
W‐‐ No.

22:52.979 --> 22:54.314
No. Maggie, no.

22:54.314 --> 22:55.399
Don't ‐‐

22:55.399 --> 22:56.858
We don't have to
talk about it right now.

22:56.858 --> 22:58.360
Y‐You're obviously
too upset.

22:58.360 --> 23:01.363
Okay, just be honest with me
and tell me the truth.

23:01.363 --> 23:02.364
[ Breathes shakily ]

23:02.364 --> 23:05.701
Did you come to Boston
to see him or me?

23:07.369 --> 23:08.412
Both.

23:08.412 --> 23:11.998
♪♪

23:11.998 --> 23:13.125
[ Voice breaking ] Okay.

23:13.125 --> 23:15.293
I'm gonna make this easy
for you.

23:15.293 --> 23:16.628
You lost Dad.

23:16.628 --> 23:18.547
Now guess what.

23:18.547 --> 23:19.631
You lost <i>me.</i>

23:19.631 --> 23:21.550
Maggie.
Maggie, wait.

23:21.550 --> 23:23.844
[ Door slams ]

23:23.844 --> 23:25.303
♪♪

23:31.393 --> 23:32.561
You nervous?

23:32.561 --> 23:33.645
Completely.

23:36.647 --> 23:38.649
Baby book's got everything
you'd ever need.

23:38.649 --> 23:39.984
Bottle warmer's
over there.

23:39.984 --> 23:41.652
If she gets too fussy,
just take her for a ride.

23:41.652 --> 23:43.446
Oh, I know the drill.

23:43.446 --> 23:45.573
Mom, you're gonna be late.
Just ‐‐ Just go, okay?

23:45.573 --> 23:47.783
Okay.
Give me a hug.

23:47.783 --> 23:48.993
[ Sighs ]

23:48.993 --> 23:50.369
You smell nice.

23:50.369 --> 23:52.705
Well, not a meeting
without perfume, is it?

23:52.705 --> 23:54.206
[ Chuckles ]

23:54.206 --> 23:55.458
It's okay, Mom.

23:55.458 --> 23:57.168
I know it's been a while
since you've had a "meeting."

23:57.168 --> 23:58.210
[ Chuckles lightly ]

23:58.210 --> 23:59.795
You're gonna do great.

23:59.795 --> 24:01.505
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you, sweetie.

24:01.505 --> 24:03.633
See? That's the better way
to handle it.

24:03.633 --> 24:04.508
Have fun.
I love you.

24:04.508 --> 24:05.593
[ Smooches ]

24:05.593 --> 24:07.553
[ Door opens, closes ]

24:07.553 --> 24:08.971
Go change.
Yeah.

24:08.971 --> 24:14.393
♪♪

24:14.393 --> 24:16.646
Mr. and Mrs. Pollock,
your table's right here.

24:16.646 --> 24:17.938
Oh, no. We're ‐‐
Yeah. Yeah.
No, we're just friends.

24:19.273 --> 24:20.316
[ Chuckles ]

24:21.942 --> 24:22.985
Thank you.

24:22.985 --> 24:24.904
[ Groans softly ]

24:24.904 --> 24:26.155
[ Sighs ]

24:28.282 --> 24:29.784
Nice.
[ Chuckles ]

24:29.784 --> 24:30.910
[ Piano plays up‐tempo music ]

24:30.910 --> 24:32.161
[ Music stops ]

24:32.161 --> 24:33.621
Man: Thanks, Elliot.
Good job.

24:34.914 --> 24:36.374
He's done.

24:36.374 --> 24:38.167
[ Whispering ]
Elliot can't sing.

24:38.167 --> 24:39.251
You're in.

24:40.920 --> 24:44.131
Well, then, I guess
all I have to do is ‐‐

24:44.131 --> 24:52.431
♪♪

24:52.431 --> 24:53.766
I changed my mind.
Let's go.

24:53.766 --> 24:55.101
What?
No. No, no, no, no.

24:55.101 --> 24:56.894
You can't quit now.

24:56.894 --> 24:58.521
[ Voice breaking ]
I can't do it.

25:01.524 --> 25:02.692
Hey, come here.

25:06.153 --> 25:07.613
[ Sighs ]

25:07.613 --> 25:09.448
Alright.

25:09.448 --> 25:10.491
Talk to me, Goose.

25:10.491 --> 25:12.535
[ Sighs ]

25:12.535 --> 25:14.286
I really liked him.

25:17.081 --> 25:18.624
[ Inhales deeply ]

25:18.624 --> 25:21.794
When he stopped talking to me,
it hurt so much.

25:23.462 --> 25:25.923
I'm sorry, man.

25:25.923 --> 25:26.966
That sucks.

25:28.426 --> 25:29.885
It's okay to cry.

25:29.885 --> 25:32.430
Probably should have done
more of that myself.

25:32.430 --> 25:36.267
And I know I told you I was
king of the breakups, but...

25:36.267 --> 25:38.519
truth is,
I got left, too.

25:38.519 --> 25:39.979
Really?
Yeah.

25:39.979 --> 25:43.357
I don't like
to think about it, but...

25:43.357 --> 25:45.067
there was Alice.

25:46.277 --> 25:47.611
She broke your heart?

25:47.611 --> 25:48.863
She did.

25:48.863 --> 25:51.449
But we cannot
let it stop us.

25:53.451 --> 25:57.204
You need to know there are
other people that will love you,

25:57.204 --> 25:58.956
and one day,
you're gonna find someone

25:58.956 --> 26:01.250
that will never <i>stop</i>
loving you.

26:03.419 --> 26:05.171
This is his loss.

26:08.048 --> 26:10.843
And all this good stuff
that you got going on in here,

26:10.843 --> 26:13.804
man, that is exactly
why you can do this.

26:13.804 --> 26:14.930
So, get in there.

26:14.930 --> 26:16.849
[ Breathing shakily ]

26:16.849 --> 26:18.559
Show him
you're the better man.

26:18.559 --> 26:20.644
[ Door opens ]

26:20.644 --> 26:22.188
Woman: Daniel Dixon?

26:24.565 --> 26:25.816
Daniel Dixon?

26:25.816 --> 26:28.277
[ Sighs ]

26:28.277 --> 26:31.405
You do know your name is
Daniel Dixon, right?

26:33.115 --> 26:35.534
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:35.534 --> 26:36.535
[ Sighs ]

26:36.535 --> 26:38.662
[ Soft music plays ]

26:42.082 --> 26:43.959
I'm, uh, glad
you were free tonight.

26:43.959 --> 26:44.960
[ Chuckles ]

26:44.960 --> 26:46.378
[ Chuckles ]

26:48.214 --> 26:49.423
And you look ‐‐
you look beautiful, by the way.

26:49.423 --> 26:50.424
Oh.
Yeah.

26:50.424 --> 26:51.300
S‐Stop it.

26:51.300 --> 26:53.344
[ Chuckles ]

26:53.344 --> 26:55.846
I'm so sorry.
I can't do this.

26:55.846 --> 26:57.640
I can't do this.
I'm so sorry.

26:57.640 --> 26:59.016
This is <i>not</i> a date.

26:59.016 --> 27:00.684
And I‐I keep
telling everybody that,

27:00.684 --> 27:01.977
and they won't believe me.

27:01.977 --> 27:04.855
And even...my son
thinks it's a date.

27:04.855 --> 27:06.315
It's okay.
<i>I</i> believe you.

27:06.315 --> 27:08.192
[ Both laugh ]

27:08.192 --> 27:09.944
I mean, it's not like
I didn't think about it.

27:09.944 --> 27:12.696
I mean, I tried on three dresses
before I picked this one.

27:12.696 --> 27:15.074
Earlier today,
I‐I changed my shirt four times,

27:15.074 --> 27:17.201
so I got you beat there.
[ Chuckles ]

27:17.201 --> 27:20.454
I'm just not...
ready for this.

27:20.454 --> 27:22.873
I'm sorry.
I'm not even close.

27:22.873 --> 27:24.041
I'm not, either.

27:24.041 --> 27:24.833
Really?

27:27.002 --> 27:29.338
But I keep thinking that it's
gonna get easier without Debra,

27:29.338 --> 27:32.049
and...

27:32.049 --> 27:33.050
hasn't yet.

27:34.426 --> 27:37.263
You don't
talk about her much.

27:37.263 --> 27:39.223
Yeah.

27:39.223 --> 27:40.808
It's difficult for me.

27:40.808 --> 27:44.687
♪♪

27:44.687 --> 27:48.107
[ "Greased Lightnin'" intro
plays ]

27:48.107 --> 27:49.858
Danny: This car
could be systematic...

27:49.858 --> 27:51.443
[ Note plays ]

27:51.443 --> 27:52.820
...Hydra‐matic...

27:52.820 --> 27:54.113
[ Note plays ]

27:54.113 --> 27:55.698
It's, uh...

27:55.698 --> 27:57.491
Can I...start again?
Man: Sure.

27:57.491 --> 28:00.119
[ "Greased Lightnin'" intro
plays ]

28:00.119 --> 28:02.162
[ Louder ]
This car could be systematic...

28:03.831 --> 28:05.374
[ Note plays ]
...Hydra‐matic...

28:06.875 --> 28:08.168
[ Note plays ]
...Ultramatic...

28:09.378 --> 28:11.380
It could be Greased Lightnin'!

28:11.380 --> 28:13.007
♪ I'll get
some overhead lifters ♪

28:13.007 --> 28:14.717
♪ And four barrel quads,
oh, yeah ♪

28:14.717 --> 28:17.428
[ Softly ] ♪ Wow, keep talkin',
wow, keep talkin' ♪

28:17.428 --> 28:18.596
Woman: Sir.
♪ With fuel injection cutoffs ♪

28:18.596 --> 28:19.680
♪ And chrome‐plated rods,
oh, yeah ♪

28:19.680 --> 28:21.348
Your big brother
is amazing.

28:22.808 --> 28:24.059
♪ With the four‐speed
on the... ♪

28:24.059 --> 28:26.312
I can't believe
you're the one who had this.

28:26.312 --> 28:27.354
You stole it.

28:27.354 --> 28:28.981
I gotta get this
back to Gary now.

28:28.981 --> 28:31.108
Burglary is a crime.
You know that, right?

28:31.108 --> 28:32.151
Look.

28:32.151 --> 28:33.652
Hairs.

28:33.652 --> 28:35.112
Okay,
i‐if I did a DNA test ‐‐

28:35.112 --> 28:36.238
You want to do what?

28:36.238 --> 28:38.824
A DNA test.
These are Jon's hairs, right?

28:38.824 --> 28:40.534
They could be Gary's,
who we know is not your dad,

28:40.534 --> 28:41.952
so if it comes back
a match ‐‐

28:41.952 --> 28:43.203
Well, don't touch it!

28:43.203 --> 28:45.289
Don't you watch
"Forensic Files"?

28:45.289 --> 28:48.042
You got to put it in
an airtight plastic bag ASAP.

28:48.042 --> 28:49.585
And ‐‐ And wrap it up

28:49.585 --> 28:51.629
and ‐‐ and ship it
to a lab somewhere.

28:51.629 --> 28:53.672
ASAP.

28:53.672 --> 28:55.299
So, you'll help me?

28:56.759 --> 28:57.718
I'll help you.

28:58.927 --> 29:00.012
But listen.

29:00.012 --> 29:01.847
If you really are
Jon's son,

29:01.847 --> 29:04.183
it's gonna change
everything.

29:04.183 --> 29:06.018
♪♪

29:06.018 --> 29:08.937
Whatever you find out,
no going back.

29:08.937 --> 29:15.152
♪♪

29:15.152 --> 29:17.529
Regina: Hmm.

29:17.529 --> 29:19.073
Okay.

29:19.073 --> 29:21.533
I got to [Chuckles] admit,
this ‐‐ the food looks good.

29:23.243 --> 29:25.079
What's this?

29:25.079 --> 29:27.790
"Andrew Pollock's discovery,
Regina Howard,

29:27.790 --> 29:31.377
Someday's executive chef, heads
her first serious restaurant."

29:31.377 --> 29:33.087
I am not his discovery.

29:33.087 --> 29:34.963
Oh, I'm sorry. I thought
it was his restaurant.

29:34.963 --> 29:36.298
It's not.

29:36.298 --> 29:38.008
It's mine
and Delilah Dixon's.

29:38.008 --> 29:40.260
Okay,
Andrew is an investor.

29:40.260 --> 29:42.846
And also, this is not
my first serious restaurant.

29:42.846 --> 29:46.225
I had a restaurant before this.
I took it just as seriously.

29:46.225 --> 29:48.477
Of course. No, I'm sorry.
I‐I'll change that.

29:48.477 --> 29:50.312
[ Breathing shakily ]

29:50.312 --> 29:52.481
You know what?
Can we just put a pin in this?

29:54.024 --> 29:56.735
I need to think about it.

29:56.735 --> 29:59.238
About everything.

29:59.238 --> 30:00.364
Thank you.
Yeah.

30:05.409 --> 30:06.702
Rome: Hey.

30:06.702 --> 30:09.038
I didn't hear you
come home.

30:09.038 --> 30:10.331
Is everything alright?

30:10.331 --> 30:12.541
No!
I'm not alright.

30:12.541 --> 30:15.461
He referred to me
as his discovery.

30:15.461 --> 30:16.712
None of this is about him.

30:16.712 --> 30:19.089
He's just doing his...job.

30:19.089 --> 30:20.549
None of <i>what</i>
is about him?

30:20.549 --> 30:22.384
This restaurant.

30:24.053 --> 30:27.973
It was a gift from Jon,
and it came from love.

30:27.973 --> 30:30.809
My mom gave me the money
from her brother.

30:30.809 --> 30:32.394
I <i>had</i> to give
Neil's money away.

30:32.394 --> 30:33.812
I'm glad I did it,

30:33.812 --> 30:35.648
but my gift should not
have been anonymous.

30:35.648 --> 30:37.650
[ Sniffles ]

30:37.650 --> 30:39.985
It's who I am, damn it.

30:39.985 --> 30:41.237
[ Sighs shakily ]

30:41.237 --> 30:42.655
I'm a survivor.

30:44.031 --> 30:47.034
And I'm going to that benefit,
and they're gonna know my name.

30:47.034 --> 30:49.912
Gina, what does this
have to do with Andrew?

30:49.912 --> 30:51.372
[ Sighs ]

30:51.372 --> 30:52.706
[ Voice breaking ]
Everything.

30:54.625 --> 30:56.710
God, it's not like
he's doing this

30:56.710 --> 30:59.588
because he cares
about my feelings.

30:59.588 --> 31:03.008
He's a businessman
in a position of power over me.

31:03.008 --> 31:06.595
♪♪

31:06.595 --> 31:09.306
I just wanted
to go a dance that night

31:09.306 --> 31:11.559
to feel liked.

31:12.851 --> 31:14.603
And that's why
I took my shirt off for him.

31:14.603 --> 31:16.021
[ Sniffles ]

31:16.021 --> 31:17.648
And I get it ‐‐
this is <i>my</i> stuff,

31:17.648 --> 31:20.025
but this is
what it feels like now.

31:20.025 --> 31:21.694
[ Sighs ]

31:21.694 --> 31:24.238
I c‐‐ I can't
take my shirt off again.

31:24.238 --> 31:25.906
I get it.

31:27.533 --> 31:29.368
And m‐my ‐‐
my first restaurant failed

31:29.368 --> 31:31.120
because I didn't do it
<i>my</i> way.

31:31.120 --> 31:32.788
I want this to succeed,
but, you know,

31:32.788 --> 31:34.623
I have to do it
on <i>my</i> terms.

31:35.874 --> 31:37.876
I know this is crazy,
but [Sniffles]

31:37.876 --> 31:40.254
I want to take out a line
of credit on our apartment,

31:40.254 --> 31:41.880
I want to give Andrew
his money back ‐‐

31:41.880 --> 31:43.090
And that's exactly
what we're gonna do.

31:44.425 --> 31:45.801
But, I mean,
we need to talk ‐‐

31:45.801 --> 31:47.636
What are you ‐‐
What are you doing?

31:47.636 --> 31:49.763
Gina,
all you been through,

31:49.763 --> 31:51.890
I can't understand
all of it,

31:51.890 --> 31:53.892
but I am at your side
for all of it.

31:53.892 --> 31:55.227
[ Clicking, cellphone beeps ]

31:55.227 --> 31:57.187
I was texting Don.

31:57.187 --> 31:58.814
I'm gonna direct
the Lexus commercials.

31:58.814 --> 32:00.316
No, Rome, you hate
directing commercials.

32:00.316 --> 32:03.777
No, I hated not knowing <i>why</i>
I was directing commercials,

32:03.777 --> 32:06.071
but at least now
I know why I'm doing it.

32:06.071 --> 32:07.781
[ Sniffles ]

32:07.781 --> 32:09.283
I'm doing it
for the love of my life.

32:09.283 --> 32:10.618
[ Exhales sharply ]

32:10.618 --> 32:11.660
[ Sniffles ]

32:11.660 --> 32:13.203
[ Sighs ]

32:13.203 --> 32:14.663
Let me help you, baby.

32:15.956 --> 32:18.083
[ Sniffling ]

32:18.083 --> 32:22.212
♪♪

32:22.212 --> 32:24.256
[ Door closes ]

32:30.929 --> 32:32.556
[ Sniffs ]
It was a Monday.

32:34.642 --> 32:36.560
My pops and I used to watch
wrestling on Mondays, but...

32:38.270 --> 32:40.731
[ Sighs ]

32:40.731 --> 32:42.983
...I heard my mother
and my father fighting.

32:45.235 --> 32:47.696
She was finally
gonna leave him.

32:47.696 --> 32:50.282
She left their bedroom,
went down the hall to my room,

32:50.282 --> 32:51.742
knocked on the door.

32:53.702 --> 32:57.122
I think she wanted
to say goodbye.

32:57.122 --> 32:58.540
But I didn't open it.

33:00.959 --> 33:02.961
I thought if I didn't answer it,
she couldn't leave.

33:04.963 --> 33:06.965
One of the greatest regrets
of my life ‐‐

33:06.965 --> 33:08.759
not answering that door.

33:10.844 --> 33:13.138
Maybe I could have
convinced her to stay.

33:16.058 --> 33:17.685
Even for a little while.

33:19.395 --> 33:20.938
So, you're right.

33:20.938 --> 33:23.399
There is a lot there
to deal with.

33:24.692 --> 33:26.568
♪♪

33:26.568 --> 33:28.195
Mm.

33:28.195 --> 33:36.495
♪♪

33:36.495 --> 33:37.621
[ Smooches ]

33:37.621 --> 33:40.624
♪♪

33:40.624 --> 33:42.960
You don't
have to worry.

33:42.960 --> 33:46.463
<i>I</i> don't give up
on the people I love.

33:46.463 --> 33:50.259
♪♪

33:50.259 --> 33:51.510
[ Chuckling ]
Except maybe...

33:53.429 --> 33:55.639
[ Sighs ]

33:55.639 --> 33:57.349
I talked to her.

33:58.517 --> 33:59.560
His name's Eric.

34:01.145 --> 34:02.354
I know
they're seeing each other.

34:02.354 --> 34:04.481
She just won't admit it.

34:04.481 --> 34:07.192
You two
just need some time.

34:09.820 --> 34:12.030
I don't know.
[ Chuckles lightly ]

34:14.533 --> 34:17.953
Our stuff goes <i>so</i> far back.

34:17.953 --> 34:22.916
♪♪

34:22.916 --> 34:23.917
[ Smooches ]

34:25.210 --> 34:26.462
[ Rock music plays ]

34:26.462 --> 34:29.298
Oof. Where'd <i>you</i> learn
how to play pool?

34:29.298 --> 34:31.925
Well, Theo has Cub Scouts
on Saturdays.

34:31.925 --> 34:33.343
Sometimes,
I would come here.

34:33.343 --> 34:34.678
It's therapeutic.

34:38.432 --> 34:40.517
So, you hustled me.

34:40.517 --> 34:41.643
[ Chuckles ]

34:41.643 --> 34:43.562
13 ball, side pocket.

34:43.562 --> 34:44.772
9 ball, corner pocket.

34:44.772 --> 34:46.523
[ Chuckles ]

34:46.523 --> 34:48.484
You sure
you want to do that?

34:48.484 --> 34:52.654
♪ It's a reason to shout ♪

34:52.654 --> 34:55.824
♪ But none of this matters
right now ♪

34:55.824 --> 34:58.118
Oh, my God!
That is incredible.

34:58.118 --> 35:00.162
[ Giggles ]

35:00.162 --> 35:01.080
Just one thing.

35:01.080 --> 35:02.206
What?

35:02.206 --> 35:03.874
You are solids.

35:03.874 --> 35:05.084
No.
Yes.

35:05.084 --> 35:06.710
I'm ‐‐

35:06.710 --> 35:09.880
[ Both laugh ]

35:09.880 --> 35:11.673
[ Laughs ]
I'm sorry.

35:11.673 --> 35:15.052
[ Laughing ]
Why did you ‐‐

35:17.888 --> 35:20.099
♪ This is the year ♪

35:20.099 --> 35:21.683
♪ This is the year ♪

35:21.683 --> 35:24.103
♪ This is the year ♪

35:24.103 --> 35:27.898
♪ Beware the darkness
around you ♪

35:27.898 --> 35:31.944
♪ They called it a killer,
they warned you what ♪

35:31.944 --> 35:35.155
This is...

35:35.155 --> 35:37.116
new territory for me.

35:37.116 --> 35:38.575
[ Sighs ]

35:38.575 --> 35:42.329
It's complicated
and weird as hell,

35:42.329 --> 35:44.790
and I can't be
any other way than confused,

35:44.790 --> 35:46.458
so...

35:46.458 --> 35:48.877
I'm gonna be sending you
mixed signals.

35:48.877 --> 35:50.045
A lot.

35:51.338 --> 35:53.549
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

35:54.842 --> 35:57.052
That's the Gilberts.
We have to go get Theo.

35:57.052 --> 35:57.886
Mm.

35:57.886 --> 36:00.139
He gave it
his best shot.

36:01.181 --> 36:03.183
Hey, um...

36:03.183 --> 36:05.102
just so you know,

36:05.102 --> 36:07.271
with all of this...

36:07.271 --> 36:09.064
I'll follow your lead.

36:09.064 --> 36:11.650
♪ Oh, this is the year ♪

36:11.650 --> 36:13.861
♪ This is the year ♪

36:13.861 --> 36:16.738
♪♪

36:22.035 --> 36:23.912
♪♪

36:23.912 --> 36:26.331
I'm sorry. I tried.

36:26.331 --> 36:27.875
I really did.

36:27.875 --> 36:30.085
But I'm pretty sure
their furnace is haunted.

36:30.085 --> 36:31.378
Are you kidding me?

36:31.378 --> 36:33.005
We missed you so much.

36:33.005 --> 36:34.506
You guys still had fun,
right?

36:34.506 --> 36:36.300
Fun?
We had a blast.

36:38.135 --> 36:40.387
I mean, as much fun as we can
have while totally missing you.

36:41.847 --> 36:44.892
Also, I was too nervous
to eat.

36:44.892 --> 36:46.643
How about pancakes?

36:48.312 --> 36:50.230
[ Keyboard clacking ]

36:53.317 --> 36:54.902
What you doing
over there?

36:54.902 --> 36:56.778
Just working
on my screenplay.

36:56.778 --> 36:58.614
[ Gasps ] Oh, my God.
I'm so sorry.

36:58.614 --> 37:00.908
I totally forgot.
How was lunch?

37:00.908 --> 37:02.492
Did Todd like it?
Yeah.

37:02.492 --> 37:04.578
He just wanted me to,
you know, make a few changes

37:04.578 --> 37:06.288
to make it more...
commercial.

37:06.288 --> 37:08.081
But that's great, right?

37:08.081 --> 37:09.333
Mm‐hmm.

37:09.333 --> 37:10.626
Except I'm not doing it.

37:12.669 --> 37:15.464
"Based on a true story."

37:15.464 --> 37:18.175
I don't want to be
anonymous anymore, either.

37:18.175 --> 37:22.971
♪♪

37:22.971 --> 37:24.056
Mm.

37:25.515 --> 37:28.018
[ Insects chirping ]

37:30.229 --> 37:32.314
[ Sighs ]

37:32.314 --> 37:34.816
[ Whispering ]
What are you still doing up?

37:34.816 --> 37:36.944
No texting in bed.
That's the rule.

37:36.944 --> 37:38.779
Sorry.

37:38.779 --> 37:40.197
How was your "meeting"?

37:40.197 --> 37:42.783
Oh, it was...

37:42.783 --> 37:44.409
not at all
what I expected,

37:44.409 --> 37:46.620
but turned out to be
exactly what I needed.

37:46.620 --> 37:48.247
Nice.

37:48.247 --> 37:51.041
Tonight wasn't exactly
what <i>I</i> expected, either.

37:51.041 --> 37:55.170
Oh, yeah. Gary told me you
had to take Charlie for a ride?

37:55.170 --> 37:56.880
Hmm?
Yeah.

37:56.880 --> 38:00.175
I got called back
for the school musical ‐‐

38:00.175 --> 38:02.219
for Kenickie in "Grease."

38:02.219 --> 38:03.553
Why didn't you tell me?

38:04.763 --> 38:06.765
Elliot auditioned
for the same part,

38:06.765 --> 38:08.517
and I just...

38:08.517 --> 38:10.560
I was embarrassed.

38:10.560 --> 38:12.813
[ Sighs ]

38:12.813 --> 38:15.899
They just posted
the cast list online.

38:15.899 --> 38:18.277
Elliot's gonna
play Kenickie.

38:19.861 --> 38:21.113
Mm.

38:21.113 --> 38:22.447
I'm sorry.

38:25.826 --> 38:27.411
Danny, I know
that you must feel ‐‐

38:27.411 --> 38:28.578
Amazing.

38:28.578 --> 38:30.372
'Cause I'm playing
Danny Zuko,

38:30.372 --> 38:32.582
who just happens to be
the lead.

38:32.582 --> 38:34.543
[ Laughs ]
You little snot!

38:34.543 --> 38:35.794
Oh!
[ Smooches ]

38:35.794 --> 38:38.338
Congratulations!

38:38.338 --> 38:41.174
Oh, I'm so happy!

38:41.174 --> 38:42.634
Me too.

38:42.634 --> 38:44.052
[ Sighs ]

38:45.929 --> 38:48.140
I miss Elliot.

38:48.140 --> 38:49.182
[ Sighs ]

38:49.182 --> 38:50.851
Danny, trust me,

38:50.851 --> 38:54.271
there will be plenty
of other Elliots out there.

38:54.271 --> 38:55.939
With his name
and everything?

38:55.939 --> 38:57.649
[ Laughs ]

38:57.649 --> 39:00.319
Oh, you're so fresh
tonight.

39:00.319 --> 39:02.696
What about you?

39:02.696 --> 39:05.115
Are there gonna be other people
out there for <i>you?</i>

39:05.115 --> 39:06.491
I don't think so.

39:08.160 --> 39:10.245
But you never know.

39:12.497 --> 39:16.835
♪ To come and wash away ♪

39:16.835 --> 39:18.295
♪ My sin and fear ♪

39:18.295 --> 39:20.380
[ <i>Line ringing</i> ]

39:20.380 --> 39:22.299
♪ I need a hero ♪

39:22.299 --> 39:24.551
<i>Hello?</i>

39:24.551 --> 39:27.054
<i>Anyone there?</i>

39:27.054 --> 39:28.138
<i>Gary?</i>

39:28.138 --> 39:32.184
♪ I need a healer ♪

39:32.184 --> 39:35.395
♪ And it doesn't
have to be medication ♪

39:35.395 --> 39:37.314
♪ It could be ♪

39:37.314 --> 39:39.149
♪ It could be ♪

39:39.149 --> 39:43.612
♪ It could be music ♪

39:43.612 --> 39:45.822
[ Water running ]

39:45.822 --> 39:49.701
♪ Oh, it could be ♪

39:49.701 --> 39:51.578
Where'd you put
the chocolate chips?

39:51.578 --> 39:53.914
They're in the other cabinet ‐‐
top shelf.

39:53.914 --> 39:54.915
Ah.

39:54.915 --> 39:56.458
We were making
chocolate chip cookies

39:56.458 --> 39:58.251
right before you had to go
to the Grand Canyon.

39:58.251 --> 39:59.836
Remember?
I do.

39:59.836 --> 40:02.130
And I'm so glad
I'm back.

40:02.130 --> 40:03.256
Me too.

40:05.550 --> 40:06.802
That's why I took
that suitcase ‐‐

40:06.802 --> 40:08.678
so you couldn't
leave again.

40:08.678 --> 40:13.892
♪ Oh, it could be music, yeah ♪

40:13.892 --> 40:15.394
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

40:15.394 --> 40:16.395
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

40:16.395 --> 40:19.439
♪ Oh‐oh‐oh‐oh‐oh ♪

40:19.439 --> 40:22.067
♪ Ah‐ah‐ah, oh‐oh‐oh ♪

40:22.067 --> 40:24.861
♪ Oh‐oh, oh‐oh, oh‐oh ♪

40:24.861 --> 40:26.488
♪ Ohhhhh ♪

40:26.488 --> 40:30.117
♪ Ohhhhhhhh, oh‐oh ♪

40:30.117 --> 40:32.494
♪♪

40:32.494 --> 40:36.540
♪ It could be ♪

40:37.958 --> 40:41.461
♪ Yeah, yeaaaaaah ♪

40:41.461 --> 40:44.214
So, what are you hoping
will come from this breakfast?

40:44.214 --> 40:45.799
What's the plan?

40:45.799 --> 40:47.926
Well, my plan is to eat
a half a dozen bagels

40:47.926 --> 40:49.803
while you try to patch things up
with your mom.

40:49.803 --> 40:52.556
What about <i>your</i> mom?
Did you call her again?

40:52.556 --> 40:54.599
You just gonna sit here
and carb‐load?

40:54.599 --> 40:56.101
No, I did not.

40:56.101 --> 40:57.519
Pass the schmear.

40:57.519 --> 40:59.688
You called her...

40:59.688 --> 41:01.273
because you want
to talk to her.

41:01.273 --> 41:02.649
[ Doorbell rings ]

41:02.649 --> 41:05.110
I guess
I have to go first, huh?

41:05.110 --> 41:06.445
[ Knock on door ]

41:06.445 --> 41:07.779
[ Colin growls, barks ]
See?

41:07.779 --> 41:09.364
<i>He</i> doesn't want her here,
either.

41:09.364 --> 41:10.740
Will you answer it?

41:10.740 --> 41:11.992
No.

41:11.992 --> 41:14.077
We're gonna answer it...

41:14.077 --> 41:15.120
together.

41:21.251 --> 41:22.335
Heeeeeey!

41:22.335 --> 41:23.420
...eeeeeeey.

41:23.420 --> 41:24.796
What is <i>he</i> doing here?

41:26.673 --> 41:28.425
I wanted you guys
to meet.

41:28.425 --> 41:30.677
You didn't tell her
I was coming?

41:32.804 --> 41:35.015
She did not.

41:35.015 --> 41:41.771
♪♪

41:46.610 --> 41:53.783
♪♪

41:53.783 --> 42:00.999
♪♪

42:00.999 --> 42:08.173
♪♪

42:08.173 --> 42:15.263
♪♪

42:15.263 --> 42:17.015
That's my boy!

42:17.015 --> 42:22.187
♪♪
